"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/999169","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2018-11-05","<p>The following information is based on the resourcing of the Employment Agency Standards Inspectorate (EAS) for the 31<sup>st</sup> March in each year:</p><p> </p><p>2015 – 5</p><p>2016 – 11</p><p>2017 – 11</p><p>2018 – 12</p><p> </p><p>The Department continues to review the resourcing needs both in the short term and in the context of wider, longer term reforms including the Taylor Review of Modern Working Practices and the strategy of the Director of Labour Market Enforcement.</p>","Rochester and Strood","Kelly Tolhurst",,"2018-11-05T17:39:10.21Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/999169/answer","Biography information for Kelly Tolhurst","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/999169/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/999169/answer",,,,,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2018-10-31","Employment Agency Standards Inspectorate: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, how many staff were employed by the Employment Agency Standards Inspectorate in (a) 2015, (b) 2016, (c) 2017 and (d) 2018.","false","Biography information for Jo Swinson","East Dunbartonshire","Jo Swinson","186255"
