"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/999388","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-11-05","<p>An administrative oversight led to the responsibilities of Justice Minister Edward Argar not being displayed on his Gov.UK profile page. His responsibilities are in line with those of his predecessor and the webpage has now been updated to show this.</p>","Charnwood","Edward Argar",,"2018-11-05T16:51:36.637Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/999388/answer","Biography information for Edward Argar","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/999388/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/999388/answer",,,,,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2018-10-31","Edward Argar","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, for what reason the ministerial responsibilities of Edward Argar are not listed on the relevant Ministry of Justice web page.","false","Biography information for Richard Burgon","Leeds East","Richard Burgon","186404"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/999389","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-11-05","<p>We are informed by NHS England that in order to ensure the best use of public funds, the National Health Service has used the procurement process to ensure that optimal value for money is achieved when purchasing drugs, which are used in secondary care.</p><p> </p><p>The NHS is working to ensure consistent use of clinically-appropriate lowest acquisition cost drugs. This has encouraged competitive pricing in return for market share. This process has allowed for an increase in the number of patients being cured within the available resources, with in excess of 30,000 patients with hepatitis C treated so far. The NHS is currently undertaking a long-term strategic procurement to increase treatment and improve value further.</p><p> </p><p>NHS England’s Commercial Medicines Unit’s six-monthly tenders, together with innovative approaches which mean the NHS is given a refund if a course of treatment does not result in cure, have succeeded in delivering reduced price per patient for all direct acting antiviral Hepatitis C drugs, such as Harvoni (ledipasvir-sofosbuvir).</p><p> </p><p>The Department has made no such estimate of the number of patients recommended the drug Harvoni by medical practitioners who have been denied access on the grounds of affordability.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine","186164","2018-11-05T15:34:31.597Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/999389/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/999389/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/999389/answer",,,,,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-10-31","Harvoni","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what steps he is taking to reduce the cost to the NHS of Harvoni; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Gareth Thomas","Harrow West","Gareth Thomas","186163"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/999390","Department for International Trade","false","2018-11-09","<p>I refer my Hon. Friend for Romford to the answers I gave to the Hon. Member for Carshalton and Wallington on 29 October 2018, UIN: 182665 and on 9 November 2018, UIN: 186919.</p>","Meon Valley","George Hollingbery",,"2018-11-09T11:46:00.317Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/999390/answer","Biography information for Sir George Hollingbery","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/999390/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/999390/answer",,,,,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2018-10-31","World Trade Organisation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, what preparations have been made for the level of representation the UK will require at the World Trade Organisation after the UK has left the EU.","false","Biography information for Andrew Rosindell","Romford","Andrew Rosindell","186242"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/999391","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-11-06","<p>The British Government is committed to the eradication of all forms of modern slavery, forced labour and human trafficking by 2030, as unanimously adopted at the UN Sustainable Development Summit in 2015. In the Democratic Republic of Congo (DRC), the UK is funding projects on the prevention of child labour in artisanal mines and on remediation work for victims of slavery in the extractive sector. We have not assessed the specific effect of levels of racism on modern slavery and human trafficking in the Great Lakes Region.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2018-11-06T13:27:47.937Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/999391/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/999391/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/999391/answer",,,,,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-10-31","Great Lakes Region: Slavery","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what recent assessment he has made of the effect of levels of racism on modern slavery and human trafficking in the African Great Lakes Region.","false","Biography information for Andrew Rosindell","Romford","Andrew Rosindell","186243"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/999392","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-11-05","<p>We are informed by NHS England that in order to ensure the best use of public funds, the National Health Service has used the procurement process to ensure that optimal value for money is achieved when purchasing drugs, which are used in secondary care.</p><p> </p><p>The NHS is working to ensure consistent use of clinically-appropriate lowest acquisition cost drugs. This has encouraged competitive pricing in return for market share. This process has allowed for an increase in the number of patients being cured within the available resources, with in excess of 30,000 patients with hepatitis C treated so far. The NHS is currently undertaking a long-term strategic procurement to increase treatment and improve value further.</p><p> </p><p>NHS England’s Commercial Medicines Unit’s six-monthly tenders, together with innovative approaches which mean the NHS is given a refund if a course of treatment does not result in cure, have succeeded in delivering reduced price per patient for all direct acting antiviral Hepatitis C drugs, such as Harvoni (ledipasvir-sofosbuvir).</p><p> </p><p>The Department has made no such estimate of the number of patients recommended the drug Harvoni by medical practitioners who have been denied access on the grounds of affordability.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine","186163","2018-11-05T15:34:31.66Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/999392/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/999392/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/999392/answer",,,,,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-10-31","Harvoni","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what estimate he has made of the number of patients recommended the drug Harvoni by medical practitioners who have been denied access to the drug on grounds of affordability; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Gareth Thomas","Harrow West","Gareth Thomas","186164"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/999393","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-11-05","<p>The Foreign Secretary has not raised this issue directly with his counterpart.</p><p>South African Government policy is to address all criminal activity with equal concern and without preferential treatment being afforded to any race or group. Our High Commission in South Africa raises issues of concern with the South African authorities where necessary, in particular where UK nationals are involved.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2018-11-05T14:23:05.57Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/999393/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/999393/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/999393/answer",,,,,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-10-31","South Africa: Farmers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what representations he has made to his South African counterpart on the provision of justice as a result of the attacks on South African farmers.","false","Biography information for Andrew Rosindell","Romford","Andrew Rosindell","186244"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/999394","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-11-05","<p>The Government responded to <em>Thriving at Work: Stevenson/Farmer Review of mental health and employers</em> in the command paper <em>Improving Lives: The Future of Work, Health and Disability</em> which was published on 30<sup>th</sup> November 2017. The joint DWP and DHSC Work and Health Unit is now overseeing progress across 40 recommendations that range from short term deliverables to longer term reform.</p><p> </p><p>We have made significant progress on ensuring the public sector leads the way: the NHS is implementing the mental health standards through the new single NHS Workforce Health and Wellbeing Framework, which was published on 16<sup>th</sup> May 2018 and shared with NHS organisations, and the Civil Service has benchmarked all main government departments and their agencies/NDPBs against the core and enhanced mental health standards to identify best practice and areas requiring further action. We also held a Public Sector Summit on 18<sup>th</sup> July 2018 which brought together public sector leaders and experts to share best practice on mental health support and how the review’s recommendations are being implemented and championed.</p><p> </p><p>We have also been progressing a range of policy work on which we will report in due course.</p><p> </p><p>We have promoted the standards to private sector employers through a range of communication channels and supported Mind in the development of their mental health at work online gateway, but data on numbers of businesses who have adopted the core and enhanced standards is not held centrally. We will continue to work with key stakeholders across the public, private and voluntary sectors to ensure that employers of all sizes act to implement the core and enhanced standards and help them, and their employees, realise the benefits of healthy, inclusive workplaces.</p>","Truro and Falmouth","Sarah Newton","186309 ; 186310","2018-11-05T17:06:31.263Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/999394/answer","Biography information for Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/999394/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/999394/answer",,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-10-31","Employment: Mental Illness","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what progress her Department has made on implementing the recommendations of the report, Thriving at Work: a review of mental health and employers, published by her Department in October 2017.","false","Biography information for Luciana Berger","Liverpool, Wavertree","Luciana Berger","186308"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/999395","Home Office","false","2018-11-07","<p>We have received a number of representations on this matter, all of which are being actively considered.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes",,"2018-11-07T16:34:04.68Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/999395/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/999395/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/999395/answer",,,,,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-10-31","Right of Abode: Veterans","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, when his Department plans to make a decision on whether to grant right of abode to former British-Hong Kong servicemen.","false","Biography information for Andrew Rosindell","Romford","Andrew Rosindell","186245"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/999396","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-11-06","<p>​As a member of the UN Security Council and the Syria Small Group, the UK is working in support of a political settlement to the conflict that protects all Syrians, including Christians and other minority groups. We have consistently called for members of religious minorities to be protected, including through the Syria resolutions at the UN Human Rights Council, on which the UK leads. We are also at the forefront of the humanitarian response to the Syria crisis, providing life-saving support to millions of Syrians from all communities, supporting them to remain in the region.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2018-11-06T17:22:47.813Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/999396/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/999396/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/999396/answer",,,,,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-10-31","Syria: Christianity","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what steps his Department has taken to enable Christians to remain in Syria.","false","Biography information for Andrew Rosindell","Romford","Andrew Rosindell","186246"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/999397","Department for International Development","false","2018-11-06","<p>The UK strongly condemns any language or actions that could stir up hatred and prejudice. Our sustained support to the Palestinian Authority (PA) is underpinned by a Memorandum of Understanding which requires the PA to commit to the principle of non-violence and to tackle language and avoid actions that could incite violence or hatred. The UK continues to urge the Palestinian leadership to uphold this principle. President Abbas restated his commitment to the two-state solution on September 27 at the UN General Assembly, and through our financial assistance, the UK will continue to support a stable PA which can act as an effective partner for peace with Israel.</p><p> </p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt","186157","2018-11-06T15:37:43.407Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/999397/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/999397/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/999397/answer",,,,,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2018-10-31","Palestinians: Politics and Government","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, with reference to her Department's Memorandum of Understanding with the Palestinian Authority (PA), what discussions her Department has had with the PA on the description on 30 June 2018 by Mahmoud Al-Habbash, an advisor to the  PA President, of Israelis and Jews as the culture of Satan.","true","Biography information for Joan Ryan","Enfield North","Joan Ryan","186156"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/999398","Department for International Development","false","2018-11-06","<p>The UK strongly condemns any language or actions that could stir up hatred and prejudice. Our sustained support to the Palestinian Authority (PA) is underpinned by a Memorandum of Understanding which requires the PA to commit to the principle of non-violence and to tackle language and avoid actions that could incite violence or hatred. The UK continues to urge the Palestinian leadership to uphold this principle. President Abbas restated his commitment to the two-state solution on September 27 at the UN General Assembly, and through our financial assistance, the UK will continue to support a stable PA which can act as an effective partner for peace with Israel.</p><p> </p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt","186156","2018-11-06T15:37:43.47Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/999398/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/999398/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/999398/answer",,,,,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2018-10-31","Palestinians: Politics and Government","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, with reference to her Department's Memorandum of Understanding with the Palestinian Authority (PA), what discussions her Department has had with the PA on the assertion on 5 October 2018 on official PA TV, that Jews dance and live on the body parts of others, and on the blood of others.","true","Biography information for Joan Ryan","Enfield North","Joan Ryan","186157"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/999399","Department for International Development","false","2018-11-05","<p>The UK strongly condemns any language or actions that could stir up hatred and prejudice. Our sustained support to the Palestinian Authority (PA) is underpinned by a Memorandum of Understanding which requires the PA to commit to the principle of non-violence and to tackle language and avoid actions that could incite violence or hatred. The UK continues to urge the Palestinian leadership to uphold this principle. President Abbas restated his commitment to the two-state solution on September 27 at the UN General Assembly, and through our financial assistance, the UK will continue to support a stable PA which can act as an effective partner for peace with Israel.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2018-11-05T14:28:09.167Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/999399/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/999399/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/999399/answer",,,,,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2018-10-31","Palestinians: Politics and Government","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, with reference to her Department's Memorandum of Understanding with the Palestinian Authority (PA), what discussions her Department has had with the PA on the assertion reported on 19 October 2018 on official PA TV, that Jews didn't learn from what Hitler did to them.","true","Biography information for Joan Ryan","Enfield North","Joan Ryan","186158"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/999400","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-11-05","<p>The Government responded to <em>Thriving at Work: Stevenson/Farmer Review of mental health and employers</em> in the command paper <em>Improving Lives: The Future of Work, Health and Disability</em> which was published on 30<sup>th</sup> November 2017. The joint DWP and DHSC Work and Health Unit is now overseeing progress across 40 recommendations that range from short term deliverables to longer term reform.</p><p> </p><p>We have made significant progress on ensuring the public sector leads the way: the NHS is implementing the mental health standards through the new single NHS Workforce Health and Wellbeing Framework, which was published on 16<sup>th</sup> May 2018 and shared with NHS organisations, and the Civil Service has benchmarked all main government departments and their agencies/NDPBs against the core and enhanced mental health standards to identify best practice and areas requiring further action. We also held a Public Sector Summit on 18<sup>th</sup> July 2018 which brought together public sector leaders and experts to share best practice on mental health support and how the review’s recommendations are being implemented and championed.</p><p> </p><p>We have also been progressing a range of policy work on which we will report in due course.</p><p> </p><p>We have promoted the standards to private sector employers through a range of communication channels and supported Mind in the development of their mental health at work online gateway, but data on numbers of businesses who have adopted the core and enhanced standards is not held centrally. We will continue to work with key stakeholders across the public, private and voluntary sectors to ensure that employers of all sizes act to implement the core and enhanced standards and help them, and their employees, realise the benefits of healthy, inclusive workplaces.</p>","Truro and Falmouth","Sarah Newton","186308 ; 186310","2018-11-05T17:06:31.31Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/999400/answer","Biography information for Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/999400/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/999400/answer",,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-10-31","Employment: Mental Illness","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many businesses have adopted the core standards set out in the report, Thriving at Work: a review of mental health and employers, published by her Department in October 2017.","false","Biography information for Luciana Berger","Liverpool, Wavertree","Luciana Berger","186309"
